I have this problem where I feel like I can't really fully enjoy anything Twokinds related until I know I won't be talking to other people for the night. (Family excepted),
I just like to get fully invested, and going back to the 'real world' straight afterwards is kind of distressing.
uhh, sometimes little things in the real world will remind me of some of the characters and such. Or like I'll have a thought of how they'd react to something.
For me a lot of it has to do with the fact that I'm living in a digs, with different people, in the middle of a city.
I may also be making a huge mistake.

I am going to go through all the Twokinds pictures-sketches, colours etc. and resave the ones I like, sorting them with names by theme or series wherever one turns up. I thought I could leave it be, but my OCD Demands it.
Probably tomorrow night, however. Or Saturday night.
